{"dataset":"articles","provider":"pursuit","banner_url":"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/fee64260e6b74d334b982b06d796c2eb49df1957e1f7ff6a34c48cacbf23.webp","id":"109582","text":"<p>Six years ago, we wondered whether <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/a-political-watershed-for-mexico\" target=\"_self\">Mexicans would shake up the establishment</a></span> and elect the first left-wing government in decades. They <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/mexicans-voted-overwhelmingly-for-change-will-they-get-it\" target=\"_self\">surely did</a></span>.</p><p class=\"left\">Now, few people can imagine another party making a home in <em>Palacio Nacional</em> (the Mexican equivalent to the “White House”) after the election on 2 June.</p><div class=\"container\" data-v-012796f8><figure class=\"ps-figure\" data-v-012796f8><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"ps-figure__image\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/varieties/64w.webp 64w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/varieties/160w.webp 160w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/varieties/375w.webp 375w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/varieties/768w.webp 768w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/varieties/960w.webp 960w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/varieties/1280w.webp 1280w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/varieties/1440w.webp 1440w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/varieties/1920w.webp 1920w\" src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/109587/fee64260e6b74d334b982b06d796c2eb49df1957e1f7ff6a34c48cacbf23.webp\" alt   data-v-012796f8><figcaption class=\"ps-figure__caption\" data-v-012796f8>Mexico’s outgoing president, Andrés Manuel López Obrador (better known as AMLO), can’t run again in these elections. Picture: Getty Images</figcaption></figure></div><h2 class=\"left\"><strong>For good or bad</strong></h2><p class=\"left\">The country’s current president, <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.britannica.com/biography/Andres-Manuel-Lopez-Obrador\" target=\"_self\">Andrés Manuel López Obrador</a></span> (better known as AMLO), has been a central figure in Mexican politics since the 90s and, while the constitution does not allow him to run again, AMLO remains the main actor in this electoral process: the 2024 General Election is basically a referendum on his government.</p><p class=\"left\">Most politicians are criticised because they break their promises; but AMLO’s main faults are to keep his, regardless of the cost.</p><p class=\"left\">For good or bad, he sticks to his guns despite challenging evidence. “<span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/08/world/americas/mexico-AMLO-economy-coronavirus.html\" target=\"_self\">I have other data</a></span>” he infamously utters.</p><!--[--><!--noindex--><article class=\"ps-cta container\" data-component=\"CallToAction\" data-v-1d83364b><div class=\"ps-cta__flex\" data-v-1d83364b><div data-v-1d83364b><img src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0030/97626/varieties/375w.jpg\" data-v-1d83364b></div></div><div class=\"ps-cta__info\" data-v-1d83364b><div class=\"ps-cta__top\" data-v-1d83364b><p class=\"ps-cta__channel ps-ff-source-sans-pro ps-fw-semibold ps-text-uppercase\" data-v-1d83364b>Politics &amp; Society</p></div><a class=\"ps-cta__link ps-ff-source-sans-pro ps-fw-semibold ps-lh-120 ps-cta__black\" href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/a-political-watershed-for-mexico?in_c=in_article_cta\" target=\"_self\" data-v-1d83364b><p data-v-1d83364b>A political watershed for Mexico? <i class=\"ps-icon--arrow-right ps-cta__black\" data-v-1d83364b></i></p></a></div></article><!--endnoindex--><!--]--><p>For this kind of attitude, he has been <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2023/02/mexico-democracy-autocrat-andres-manuel-lopez-obrador/673137/\" target=\"_self\">depicted</a></span> as a populist leader with authoritarian impulses. Stories are seldom that simple, though.</p><p class=\"left\">It is true that AMLO regularly <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://cpj.org/2023/05/mexican-president-lopez-obrador-repeatedly-criticizes-news-outlets-and-press-freedom-group-over-spyware-coverage/\" target=\"_self\">thrashes</a></span> his detractors in public, that his austerity measures <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://animalpolitico.com/politica/austeridad-gasto-carreteras-suben-accidentes\" target=\"_self\">unnecessarily cost lives</a></span>, and that he has handed too much power and authority to the <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/11/world/americas/mexico-2024-general-election.html#link-544caec2\" target=\"_self\">military forces</a></span>.</p><p class=\"left\">However, AMLO also brought wages to an <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.coneval.org.mx/Medicion/Paginas/ITLP-IS_pobreza_laboral.aspx#:~:text=El ingreso laboral real per,comparación con el ámbito rural.\" target=\"_self\">all-time high</a></span>, delivered a <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/travel/2023/12/21/mexico-maya-train-tickets-faq/\" target=\"_self\">world-class tourist train</a></span>, and built an <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/mexico-aims-to-compete-with-panama-canal-by-using-cargo-trains\" target=\"_self\">interoceanic corridor</a></span>. Fulfilling yet another of his campaign promises, AMLO’s government <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.americasquarterly.org/article/the-real-reasons-for-amlos-popularity/\" target=\"_self\">transfers cash</a></span> to 14 million families.</p><p class=\"left\">Importantly, it is the poorest people in Mexico who benefit the most; his policies have taken 3.5 million people <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://english.elpais.com/economy-and-business/2024-02-15/how-did-mexico-reduce-economic-inequality.html\" target=\"_self\">out of poverty</a></span> (a 52 per cent increase over previous administrations).</p><div class=\"container\" data-v-012796f8><figure class=\"ps-figure\" data-v-012796f8><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"ps-figure__image\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/varieties/64w.webp 64w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/varieties/160w.webp 160w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/varieties/375w.webp 375w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/varieties/768w.webp 768w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/varieties/960w.webp 960w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/varieties/1280w.webp 1280w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/varieties/1440w.webp 1440w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/varieties/1920w.webp 1920w\" src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0029/109586/c02cd75e3dea37b08a05ff4baef567f210a3ac5531582b682d3cdea15ed3.webp\" alt   data-v-012796f8><figcaption class=\"ps-figure__caption\" data-v-012796f8>Claudia Sheinbaum —established academic and former Mexico City mayor— is AMLO’s protégée. Picture: Getty Images</figcaption></figure></div><p>Rather than nuance the evaluation of his government, AMLO’s low lows and high highs seem to entice people’s support, as if they find some beauty in this political chiaroscuro (or contrast).</p><p class=\"left\">Perhaps the tipping point is AMLO’s <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.aljazeera.com/features/longform/2024/3/29/mexico-debates-a-rising-political-partys-new-deal-for-the-poor\" target=\"_self\">modest demeanour</a></span>.</p><p class=\"left\">Unlike the opulent lifestyle of his predecessors, AMLO takes the bus and stops at convenience stores to buy snacks or simply chats with people. He also visits remote and poor villages where no Mexican president has shown up before.</p><!--[--><!--noindex--><article class=\"ps-cta container\" data-component=\"CallToAction\" data-v-1d83364b><div class=\"ps-cta__flex\" data-v-1d83364b><div data-v-1d83364b><img src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0028/97516/varieties/375w.jpg\" data-v-1d83364b></div></div><div class=\"ps-cta__info\" data-v-1d83364b><div class=\"ps-cta__top\" data-v-1d83364b><p class=\"ps-cta__channel ps-ff-source-sans-pro ps-fw-semibold ps-text-uppercase\" data-v-1d83364b>Politics &amp; Society</p></div><a class=\"ps-cta__link ps-ff-source-sans-pro ps-fw-semibold ps-lh-120 ps-cta__black\" href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/mexicans-voted-overwhelmingly-for-change-will-they-get-it?in_c=in_article_cta\" target=\"_self\" data-v-1d83364b><p data-v-1d83364b>Mexicans voted overwhelmingly for change. Will they get it? <i class=\"ps-icon--arrow-right ps-cta__black\" data-v-1d83364b></i></p></a></div></article><!--endnoindex--><!--]--><p>Arguably, his personality alone has boosted Mexicans’ <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.latinobarometro.org/lat.jsp?Idioma=0\" target=\"_self\">satisfaction</a></span> with their democracy and <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.inegi.org.mx/programas/encig/2021/#tabulados\" target=\"_self\">trust</a></span> in their government, because the hard data reveals that <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://americasquarterly.org/article/the-real-reasons-for-amlos-popularity/\" target=\"_self\">violence</a></span> and <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/11/world/americas/mexico-2024-general-election.html\" target=\"_self\">corruption</a></span> have not decreased significantly.</p><h2 class=\"left\"><strong>The election of 20,000</strong></h2><p class=\"left\">The 2024 General Elections will be <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.as-coa.org/articles/mexico-elects-whats-play-countrys-massive-elections\" target=\"_self\">the largest in Mexican history</a></span>.</p><p class=\"left\">More than 20,000 posts are up for grabs – including the presidency and several state governorships. But violence has tainted the electoral process, with dozens of candidates killed; the current campaign is likely to become the <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.wilsoncenter.org/article/mexicos-next-president-will-face-security-emergency-cant-be-ignored\" target=\"_self\">deadliest ever</a></span>.</p><p class=\"left\">Violence is seen as a <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://elpais.com/mexico/elecciones-mexicanas/2024-03-07/la-inseguridad-se-perfila-como-la-gran-batalla-electoral-entre-el-oficialismo-y-la-oposicion-en-mexico.html\" target=\"_self\">top election issue</a></span> and, while all candidates promise to end “narco politics” (the interference of cartels in political life), illegal campaign financing is an ongoing concern and some criminal groups even field their <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.wilsoncenter.org/article/mexicos-next-president-will-face-security-emergency-cant-be-ignored\" target=\"_self\">own candidates.</a></span></p><p class=\"left\">While there are three presidential candidates, Mexico will elect its first female president, unless something extraordinary happens.</p><div class=\"container\" data-v-012796f8><figure class=\"ps-figure\" data-v-012796f8><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"ps-figure__image\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/varieties/64w.webp 64w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/varieties/160w.webp 160w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/varieties/375w.webp 375w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/varieties/768w.webp 768w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/varieties/960w.webp 960w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/varieties/1280w.webp 1280w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/varieties/1440w.webp 1440w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/varieties/1920w.webp 1920w\" src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/109583/2cb252c5b2ba483a100b8d9d8f576ab515dcfd5167ed6f92fc0c4c60f8cd.webp\" alt   data-v-012796f8><figcaption class=\"ps-figure__caption\" data-v-012796f8>Xóchitl Gálvez is the opposition’s last resort against AMLO. Picture: Getty Images</figcaption></figure></div><p>The race is led by two women: <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.britannica.com/biography/Claudia-Sheinbaum\" target=\"_self\">Claudia Sheinbaum</a></span> and <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.wilsoncenter.org/article/candidate-profile-xochitl-galvez-ruiz\" target=\"_self\">Xóchitl Gálvez</a></span>, and the only male candidate,<span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://5g.wilsoncenter.org/article/candidate-profile-jorge-alvarez-maynez\" target=\"_self\"> Jorge Álvarez Máynez</a></span>, critically lags behind.</p><p class=\"left\">Sheinbaum —established academic and former Mexico City mayor— is AMLO’s protégée and has promised to continue <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/11/world/americas/mexico-2024-general-election.html#link-544caec2\" target=\"_self\">his agenda</a></span>: consolidating his major infrastructure projects, carrying out his austerity measures and preserving his social welfare programs.</p><p class=\"left\">Sheinbaum’s job as mayor is <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www-statista-com.eu1.proxy.openathens.net/statistics/1396278/approval-rate-claudia-sheinbaum-governmental-postion-mexico-city/#:~:text=However, as of June 2023,over half of the population.\" target=\"_self\">approved by many</a></span> but not without <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-56977129\" target=\"_self\">scandals</a></span>.</p><!--[--><!--noindex--><article class=\"ps-cta container\" data-component=\"CallToAction\" data-v-1d83364b><div class=\"ps-cta__flex\" data-v-1d83364b><div data-v-1d83364b><img src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0028/96562/varieties/375w.jpg\" data-v-1d83364b></div></div><div class=\"ps-cta__info\" data-v-1d83364b><div class=\"ps-cta__top\" data-v-1d83364b><p class=\"ps-cta__channel ps-ff-source-sans-pro ps-fw-semibold ps-text-uppercase\" data-v-1d83364b>Politics &amp; Society</p></div><a class=\"ps-cta__link ps-ff-source-sans-pro ps-fw-semibold ps-lh-120 ps-cta__black\" href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/brazil-elections-is-democracy-itself-on-the-ballot?in_c=in_article_cta\" target=\"_self\" data-v-1d83364b><p data-v-1d83364b>Brazil elections: Is democracy itself on the ballot? <i class=\"ps-icon--arrow-right ps-cta__black\" data-v-1d83364b></i></p></a></div></article><!--endnoindex--><!--]--><p>In any case, she has a record of being more progressive than her leader in social issues that are still controversial in Mexico, including abortion.</p><p class=\"left\">Unlike AMLO, who tended to conservatism on cultural issues, Sheinbaum is seen as a <em>real</em> left-wing candidate.</p><p class=\"left\">Gálvez is the opposition’s last resort against AMLO.</p><p class=\"left\">She leads a multi-party coalition that has <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/11/world/americas/mexico-2024-general-election.html#link-544caec2\" target=\"_self\">pledged</a></span> to undo AMLO’s mistakes: defend institutionalised democratic checks and balances, demilitarise the country and withdraw the armed forces from civilian duties.</p><p class=\"left\">For many voters, however, she carries the weight of being endorsed by the parties responsible for the decades of corruption in Mexico.</p><div class=\"container\" data-v-012796f8><figure class=\"ps-figure\" data-v-012796f8><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"ps-figure__image\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/varieties/64w.webp 64w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/varieties/160w.webp 160w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/varieties/375w.webp 375w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/varieties/768w.webp 768w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/varieties/960w.webp 960w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/varieties/1280w.webp 1280w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/varieties/1440w.webp 1440w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/varieties/1920w.webp 1920w\" src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0027/109584/9424910e490d74b8723c45b77142e49c370f237b6bc2c53a89266aca7431.webp\" alt   data-v-012796f8><figcaption class=\"ps-figure__caption\" data-v-012796f8>Jorge Álvarez Máynez critically lags behind in the latest polling. Picture: Getty Images</figcaption></figure></div><p>According to <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://oraculus.mx/presidente2024/\" target=\"_self\">most polls</a></span>, Sheinbaum is leading the presidential race by at least 20 per cent. Her imminent victory has led some <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.as-coa.org/articles/mexico-elects-ongoing-coverage-2024-vote\" target=\"_self\">to call</a></span> for the third candidate to decline in Gálvez’s favour.</p><p class=\"left\">It is Sheinbaum versus the world now, and she will probably win.</p><h2 class=\"left\"><strong>The stakes for Australia</strong></h2><p class=\"left\">Some might argue that geographical distance makes this election irrelevant for Australia.</p><p>While it might be true that Australia has more pressing geopolitical worries, it is also true that Mexico is shaping up to be a regional leader.</p><p class=\"left\">AMLO’s motto “<span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.americasquarterly.org/article/amlos-foreign-policy-moment/\" target=\"_self\">the best foreign policy is a good domestic policy</a></span>” was supposed to guide his foreign policy to impartiality, if not indifference, to world affairs.</p><p class=\"left\">However, his government has taken some major diplomatic decisions, like offering political asylum to <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-50397922\" target=\"_self\">Bolivia’s Evo Morales</a></span> (the deposed president) and proposing <span class=\"underline\"><a href=\"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2021/11/9/mexico-amlo-proposes-global-anti-poverty-plan-un-speech\" target=\"_self\">a global anti-poverty plan</a></span> before the UN Security Council.</p><p class=\"left\">In a relatively unstable international arena, polarised by countries like China and the US, Australia would do well to keep an eye on Mexico’s future president.</p>\n<p>This article was first published on <a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au\">Pursuit</a>. <a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/it-s-worth-keeping-an-eye-on-mexico-s-future-president\">Read the original article.</a></p>","date_published":"2024-05-24T00:00:00+10:00","date_updated":"2024-05-24T00:00:00+10:00","url":"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/it-s-worth-keeping-an-eye-on-mexico-s-future-president","title":"It’s worth keeping an eye on Mexico’s future president","summary":"Mexico’s 2024 General Election will be the largest in the country’s history with around 20,000 posts up for grabs – but the key race is the one to Palacio Nacional","org_objects":[],"tag_objects":[],"author_objects":[{"name":"Dr Ren\\u00e9 Rej\\u00f3n","url":"https:\\/\\/pursuit.unimelb.edu.au\\/individuals\\/dr-rene-rejon","orcid":"","fae_url":"https://findanexpert.unimelb.edu.au/profile/836491-rene-rejon","email":""}],"citation_objects":[{"credentials":"Dr Ren\\u00e9 Rej\\u00f3n"}]}